        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:07PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pierrepont, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Potsdam Village, Brasher, Pierrepont, Parishville, Lawrence,
Stockholm, Dickinson, Potsdam, Moira, Norfolk, Canton, Hopkinton,
Clare, Russell, Colton, North Stockholm, West Parishville, Brasher
Center, West Stockholm, and Nicholville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
